TextPart(
    type='text',
    text='Done. I identified and fixed **2 E2E bugs** that would cause test fail
ures for Issue #64:\n\n### Bug 1: Maestro identifier mismatch in `matching/view_
match_list.yaml`\n**Root cause**: The flow asserted `id: "match_list_item"`, but
`MatchListPage` was upgraded to use `SwConversationListItem` which exposes `id: 
"conversation_item"`. This caused the E2E test to silently skip the list-item as
sertion (due to `optional: true`) even when conversations existed.\n\n**Fix**: R
eplaced the optional `assertVisible` with a conditional `runFlow` that uses the 
correct identifier `conversation_item`, referencing the existing IM assertion pa
rtial.\n\n### Bug 2: `run-e2e.sh` incorrectly included partial `_*.yaml` files\n
**Root cause**: When running all Maestro flows, the script\'s `find` commands co
llected every `.yaml` file under `.maestro/flows/`, including partial files like
`_conversation_list_assertions.yaml` and `_enter_chat_actions.yaml`. These parti
als are not standalone tests and would fail when executed independently.\n\n**Fi
x**: Added `-not -name "_*.yaml"` to both `find` commands in the script so parti
al include files are excluded from the test execution list.\n\n### Verification\
n- ✅ `make arch-check` passed\n- ✅ `bash .maestro/scripts/maestro-check.sh` pa
ssed\n- ✅ `flutter analyze` — no issues\n- ✅ `flutter test` — all 48 tests pas
sed\n- ✅ `find` output verified — only actual test flows are included, no parti
als\n- ✅ Committed and pushed to `origin/feat/issue-5`\n- ✅ `git status` is cl
ean'
)
